annotationA: Regulatory particle triple-A ATPase 4 (Rpt4) is the 19S proteasomal ATPase, which is a component of the 26S proteosome complex. Rpt4 localizes to the nucleolus and participates in regulating rRNA transcription. Rpt4 physically interacts with the BHD tumor suppressor
annotationB: Protein numb; Required in determination of cell fate during sensory organ formation in embryos. Functions in nuclei and seems to interact with nucleic acids
